-- Copper Futures in London Gain for First Day in Three, Erase Earlier Loss
-- Glenys Sim
-- 2010-07-19T00:25:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/copper-futures-in-london-gain-for-first-day-in-three-erase-earlier-loss.html

          
          
             Copper in London gained for the
first time in three days, by as much as 0.3 percent, to $6,503 a
metric ton. The contract for delivery in three months on the
London Metal Exchange earlier fell as much as 0.2 percent to a
two-week low, before trading at $6,502 a ton by 8:25 a.m. in
Singapore.  
          
          


  


        